%*ENV
variable dynamic hash
access to operating system environment variables
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#%*ENV
A hash that contains all of the environment variables of the operating
system when Raku is started.  May be altered.  Serves as a default for
environment variables for any forked process.

$*PID
variable dynamic integer
the Process IDentifier
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*PID
An integer value for the PID of the current process.

$*USER
variable dynamic integer string
the current user
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*USER
An C<IntStr> with information about the current user (uid and name).

$*GROUP
variable dynamic integer string
the group of the current user
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*GROUP
An C<IntStr> with group information about the current user (gid and
name) if supported by the operating system.

$*DISTRO
variable dynamic
operating system information
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*DISTRO
A C<Distro> object containing the information about the operating
system under which this process is running.

$*KERNEL
variable dynamic
kernel information
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*KERNEL
A C<Kernel> object containing the information about the kernel
under which this process is running.

$*HOMEDRIVE
variable dynamic
home drive of user
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*HOMEDRIVE
Windows only: an C<IO::Path> object of the home drive of the user,
based on the C<HOMEDRIVE> environment variable.

$*HOMEPATH
variable dynamic
home path of user
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*HOMEPATH
Windows only: an C<IO::Path> object of the home path of the user,
based on the C<HOMEPATH> environment variable.

$*HOME
variable dynamic
generic home directory
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*HOME
An C<IO::Path> object of the home directory of the user, based on
the C<HOME>, C<HOMEDRIVE> and C<HOMEPATH> environment variable
as appropriate for the operating system in use.

$*TMPDIR
variable dynamic
directory for temporary files
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*TMPDIR
An C<IO::Path> object that can be used to store temporary files.

$*SPEC
variable dynamic
OS specific path semantics
https://docs.raku.org/language/variables#$*SPEC
An C<IO::Spec> subclass object containing any specific path semantics
of the operating system.


contains all dynamic variables related to the actual hardware
/ software the current process is running under.
